<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFF9FFD8A5CDFBB31D30FA41" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFF9FFD8A5CDFBB31C7DFB44" blockId="9.[136,578,1130,1157]" box="[136,578,1130,1157]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<heading id="D0A781CFFFF9FFD8A5CDFBB31C7DFB44" box="[136,578,1130,1157]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" reason="4">
3. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFF9FFD8A5E1FBB31C01FB44" authority="Nees &amp; Martius (1823: 73)" authorityName="Nees &amp; Martius" authorityPageNumber="73" authorityYear="1823" box="[164,574,1130,1157]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Casselia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF9FFD8A5E1FBB31F3BFB45" bold="true" box="[164,260,1130,1157]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Casselia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF9FFD8A449FBB21C01FB44" author="Nees von Esenbeck, C. G. D. &amp; Martius, C. F. P." box="[268,574,1130,1157]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="73 - 76" refId="ref36369" refString="Nees von Esenbeck, C. G. D. &amp; Martius, C. F. P. (1823) Beitrag zur Flora Braziliens. Nova Acta Physico-Medica Academiae Caesareae Leopoldino-Carolinae Naturae Curiosum 11: 73 - 76." type="journal article" year="1823">Nees &amp; Martius (1823: 73)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFF9FFD8A5CDFB6B1D30FA41" blockId="9.[136,1452,1202,1624]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Subshrubs, monoecious, branches without prickles, not aromatic. Leaves petiolate, glands near to the petiole absent. Inflorescences axillary, simple, racemes reduced to two flowers, rachis absent; bracts membranaceous, green; bracteoles absent. Flowers pedicellate; calyx campanulate, shorter than the corolla, membranaceous, green, 5-lobed, not accrescent in fruit; corolla zygomorphic, 5-lobed; stamens 4, included, didynamous, superior pair with glandular thickness in the connective, thecae divergent; ovary 1-carpelate, 2-loculate, ovules 1 per locule, stigma oblique, papillose. Fruit a schizocarp, with 2 cluses, brown, external surface rugose.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFF9FFD8A5F8FA531EF0F998" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFF9FFD8A5F8FA531EF0F998" blockId="9.[136,1452,1202,1624]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFF9FFD8A5F8FA531F22FA64" authorityName="Nees &amp; Martius" authorityYear="1823" box="[189,285,1418,1444]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Casselia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF9FFD8A5F8FA531F22FA64" box="[189,285,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Casselia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is part of the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFF9FFD8A4B5FA531D06FA64" authority="(Marx et al. 2010)" baseAuthorityName="Marx" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[496,825,1418,1444]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Casselieae">
Casselieae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF9FFD8A731FA531D0EFA64" author="Marx, H. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; Yuan, Y. &amp; Lu-Irving, P. &amp; Tank, D. &amp; Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R." box="[628,817,1418,1444]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1647 - 1663" refId="ref35509" refString="Marx, H., O'Leary, N., Yuan, Y., Lu-Irving, P., Tank, D., Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R. (2010) A molecular phylogeny and classification of Verbenaceae. American Journal of Botany 97: 1647 - 1663. https: // doi. org / 10.3732 / ajb. 1000144" type="journal article" year="2010">
Marx 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF9FFD8A7FCFA521CCEFA64" box="[697,753,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and presents six species endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFF9FFD8A194FA531B19FA64" box="[1233,1318,1418,1444]" name="Bolivia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFF9FFD8A074FA531B47FA64" box="[1329,1400,1418,1444]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFF9FFD8A5CDFA761ECEFA09" box="[136,241,1455,1481]" name="Paraguay" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, restrict to the 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF9FFD8A4D1FA771FCCFA08" box="[404,499,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Cerrado</emphasis>
and Atlantic Forest (O’Leary &amp; Múlgura 2010, Cardoso 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF9FFD8A12BFA761B35FA08" box="[1134,1290,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al. in press.</emphasis>
). The genus is characterized by the presence of campanulate calyx and drupaceous, dry at maturity, schizocarpic not ornamented fruit, partially inserted inside the persistent calyx (O’Leary &amp; Múlgura 2010). All six species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFF9FFD8A1DBFA2F1AC1F9D0" authorityName="Nees &amp; Martius" authorityYear="1823" box="[1182,1278,1526,1552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Casselia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF9FFD8A1DBFA2F1AC1F9D0" box="[1182,1278,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Casselia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
growin 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFF9FFD8A025FA2F1B98F9D0" box="[1376,1447,1526,1552]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and five of them are endemic (O’Leary &amp; Múlgura 2010, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF9FFD8A649F9C31A02F9F4" author="O'Leary, N. &amp; Boldorini, A." box="[780,1085,1562,1588]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refId="ref36459" refString="O'Leary, N. &amp; Boldorini, A. (2020) Casselia in Flora do Brasil 2020 under construction. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 21413 (accessed 4 January 2021)" type="url" year="2020">O’Leary &amp; Boldorini 2020</bibRefCitation>
). There is one species in 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFF9FFD8A016F9C31EF4F998" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
